-- Africa Industries Gains Most in a Month on Distribution Deal
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-05-29T09:41:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-29/africa-industries-gains-most-in-a-month-on-distribution-deal-1-.html
Africa Israel Industries Ltd. (AFID)  rose
the most in more than a month after the maker and importer of
steel coils and ceramic tiles said a unit signed a distribution
agreement with a Canadian company.  Africa  shares  advanced 3.5 percent, the most since April 10
in intraday trade, to 252.50 shekels at 11:41 a.m. in  Tel Aviv .  The company said its Negev Ceramics Ltd. unit signed a 400
million-shekel ($103.3 million) distribution pact with Olympia
Tile International Inc., a construction materials manufacturer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
 ssolomon22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
